title: For Sale:  Bulgarian AK-47 SSR-85C-2
postcontent: These guns were built in Bulgaria with a Bulgarian-made 1.6mm receiver and Bulgarian military parts. Then they were imported by a company called Armory USA, in Houston, TX. These are not "parts guns" that were imported as kits and then assembled in the US -- they are genuine Eastern bloc AKs. The receiver is a bit thicker than the standard 1mm AK receiver. The gun has a 16-inch chrome-lined barrel, and it has all matching parts (receiver, bolt, and rear sight leaf.)On the left side of the receiver, it says "SSR-85C-2, Cal. 7.62x39 mm, Armory USA, Houston, TX." On the right side of the receiver under the trunnion, it says "ISD Bulgaria LTD, Made in Bulgaria."The gun is in great shape, and I've updated it with the following items:1) Hogue pistol grip2) ATI Strikeforce 6-position adjustable stock with adjustable/removable cheek rest3) Tapco G2 trigger group (eliminates the infamous AK trigger slap)4) A rear sight with a slightly widened notch, for easier target acquisition. (The original numbered rear sight is also included.)The gun also comes with the original cleaning kit, a standard US-made plastic buttstock, six 30-round Eastern bloc steel magazines (five of which are like new), two 20-round like-new Tapco magazines, and a Maglula magazine loader/unloader. Three of the mags have followers installed that enable you to lock the bolt open.This is not an "entry level" AK; these guns have a reputation for very solid build quality and very good accuracy. Feel free to read up on them.Asking $850 shipped to your FFL anywhere in the Continental US. I will not break up the package. No trades. Paypal is preferred.I have more pictures, so if you are interested or have any questions, contact me and I'll send you all the photos.Thanks for looking.
